result.execSummary:
Royma Hampton was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Royma Hampton was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Colleen Taylor appeared to notify Court that defendant has been extradited and case can be closed.

Defendant Royma Hampton via Zoom with Meghan DeVol appears under student practice rule supervised by attorney Colleen A Taylor.  Defendant Royma Hampton in custody.  Alexander James Geocaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Franke, Branch 25 reserve.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Virginia.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for July 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Colleen A Taylor in court, defendant Royma Hampton not in court, in custody.  Stephan Eduard Nolten appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for a bail bond hearing. Bail motion by defense argued and DENIED by the Court. Court ordered ocntinued REMDAND of the defendant. Case adjourned to Branch 28.
Per Chief Judge Directive 22-04 effective June 13, 2022, this calendar will be assigned to Reserve Judge John Franke, in Room 608 of the Courthouse.

Defendant Royma Hampton in court with attorney Colleen A Taylor.  Defendant Royma Hampton in custody.  William R. F. Ackell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Royma Hampton appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Sanders, Branch 28.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of VIRGINIA.  Defendant contested extradition.  DEFENDANT IS NOT INDIGENT.  Court ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Defense request to be heard on bail.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for May 27, 2022 at 09:00 am.  Status conference scheduled for June 21, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
